1954;;You Know What Sailors Are;;British;;Ken Annakin;;Donald Sinden, Akim Tamiroff;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/You_Know_What_Sailors_Are_(1954_film);;Three British naval officers out on a drunken spree attach a pram and a pawnbroker's sign to the stern of a foreign naval ship. The next morning, an officer misinterprets the pram and sign as state of the art, top-secret radar equipment. Instantly, the British navy decrees that their ships be fitted with the same device. Thereafter, bureaucratic misunderstandings escalate into a major international incident.